<br>
You can be a trader and make money as a middleman.  I can't do that, but know of some who make lots of cash that way.  You need to keep track of actual prices.  Most people who sell in EC don't know the real price of things (myself included).  Knowledge is money.<br>
<br>
You hunt cash critters.  Hill giants are the typical cash cow.  Get a group and head to Rathe Mountains.<br>
<br>
Hunt in dungeons and hope to get rares.  As a cleric, this seems like the best solution for you.  Also, look for the dungeons that have the stuff you need.  While 147 wisdom is OK for level 37, you should be closer to 200.<br>
<br>
The cleric quest armor is pretty expensive (in terms of enchanted platinum bars) for when you get them.  As a druid, the only quest item I got was the Acolyte's Anklet at level 19 -- and it didn't cost anything.  Some classes are just high maintenence.<br>
